<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a1df102-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6855"><num value="6855">§ 6855.</num><heading> Cooperation and coordination</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id7a1df103-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6855/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Third-party providers</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretaries may enter into an agreement with a third party to carry out any provision of this chapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id7a1df104-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6855/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> US Geological Survey</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretaries shall work with the Director of the United States Geological Survey to collect, aggregate, digitize, standardize, or publish data on behalf of the Secretaries to meet the requirements of this chapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id7a1df105-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/117/114/s6">Pub. L. 117–114, § 6</ref>, <date date="2022-04-29">Apr. 29, 2022</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/136/1177">136 Stat. 1177</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/118/234/tIII/s354/3">Pub. L. 118–234, title III, § 354(3)</ref>, <date date="2025-01-04">Jan. 4, 2025</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/138/2917">138 Stat. 2917</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id7a1df106-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id7a1df107-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id7a1df108-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2025—Subsec. (b). <ref href="/us/pl/118/234">Pub. L. 118–234</ref> substituted “shall” for “may” and “the Secretaries” for “the Secretary of the Interior”.</p>
</note>
</notes>
